questions.text: What is your overall impression of this course?

parts.text: First, what is your overall impression of this course?
Yo, it's pretty good.
Great! Thanks. Next, how effective was the instructor in conveying the course material?
Nah, dude, I saw. Who are you buy doing?
I'm conducting a student survey about the course.  Could you tell me how effective the instructor was in conveying the course material?
He was pretty good.
Okay, thanks!  How would you rate the workload for this course?  Was it light, moderate, or heavy?
Pretty heavy I would say. Don't you think that's bad?
I understand your concern about the workload.  We're just gathering data for the survey.  Thanks for sharing your thoughts.  Moving on, what aspects of the course did you find most helpful?
Do you have any observations Alex?
I'm sorry, I'm focusing on the survey right now. What aspects of the course did you find most helpful?
Nothing much.
Okay.  What aspects of the course could be improved?
I don't know.
That's alright.  How engaged were you in class? Would you say very engaged, somewhat engaged, or not very engaged?
Not winning.
Okay. To clarify, would you say you were not very engaged in class?
Yes, I was not really engaged in class.
Thank you. Last question: Would you recommend this course to other students?
Absolutely not.
Okay.
Great!  Is there anything else I can help you with today?
